Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from
greens; mince greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1%unit}. Dice @tomato{1%unit} into
1-inch pieces. Slice @grilling cheese{8%ounce} into four pieces.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring
to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Creamy Lemon Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, minced scallion greens,
@olive oil{1%teaspoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and lemon zest to taste; stir until
smooth. Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste
and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Sunflower Seeds & Marinated Tomato ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large heavy-bottomed pan{} over
medium heat. Add @sunflower seeds{1/2%ounce} and a pinch of salt and pepper; cook,
stirring occasionally, until golden brown and toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off
heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss tomato with @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon
juice, and a pinch of @sugar{pinch}. Season with salt and pepper.

== Tempura Batter & Cheese ==

In a second medium bowl, whisk together @tempura batter{82%g}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon},
1/3 cup cold water, and a pinch of salt and pepper.

> TIP: If batter is too thick, add more water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches a
> pancake-batter-like consistency.

Add grilling cheese to bowl with batter; toss to fully coat.

== Frying Cheese ==

Heat 1/3-inch layer of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in pan used for sunflower seeds over
medium heat. Once oil is shimmering and hot enough that a drop of batter sizzles when
added to the pan, add coated grilling cheese. Cook until golden brown,
~{2-3%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Work in batches if necessary.

Using #tongs{}, transfer to a paper-towel-lined plate or #baking sheet{}.

== To Serve ==

Add @mixed greens{2%ounce} to bowl with marinated tomato; toss to combine. Taste and
season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Divide rice and salad between #bowls{} in separate
sections. Top with grilling cheese. Drizzle with sauce and sprinkle with sunflower
seeds. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.